						<summary>

						<p>CHIDAMBARAM, CHIDAMBARAM TALUK, SOUTH ARCOT DISTRICT.</p>						

						<p>Naṭarāja temple, west <hi rend="italic">gōpuram,</hi> right of entrance.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Sundara-pāṇḍya ••• •••</hi></p>						

						<p>Contains two Tamil verses referring to the performance of the <hi rend="italic">tulābhāram</hi> ceremony (in which a person is weighed against gold or any other commodity) by Sundarapāṇḍya in the gift of the gold of his weight, to the temple, probably for gilding it.</p>						

						</summary>
